[SN]TITLE[SN]
Welsh artist Ogwyn Davies dies aged 90

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Artist Ogwyn Davies has died, his family has confirmed.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Mr Davies, 90, whose paintings were inspired by buildings from Welsh landscapes, died on 26 December.
One of his most famous works was Soar y Mynydd, which depicts a chapel in Ceredigion, near where he lived.
Born in 1925 in Trebanos, Neath Port Talbot, Mr Davies studied at Swansea School of Art before working at Tregaron Comprehensive, Ceredigion.
